<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <head>No. 135.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">Flores</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilmington, Del.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-04"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 4, 1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Understanding from your announcement of amnesty that Santos is now at
                            liberty to come home, the Iroquois will be recalled.</p>
                        <p>Show this to Mr. Adee.</p>
                        <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>